cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to detect subjective bias in text. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses BERT-based models, which are a type of deep learning model, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with information retrieval and content recommendation, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
